      "num": 1,
      "name": "FOUNDATION FORGE",
      "tagline": "Build the Engine",
      "weeks": "Weeks 1–5",
      "focuses": [
        "Build baseline strength in compound lifts and establish progressive core overload.",
        "Ingrain movement quality, lock in consistent training habits, and initiate a sustainable caloric deficit."
      ],
      "message": {
        "paragraphs": [
          "This cycle sets the ceiling for everything that follows. The strength, stability, and habits you build here determine how much volume, density, and intensity your body can tolerate later.",
          "Your joints, connective tissue, and nervous system are adapting to structured compound loading while your core is learning to handle real demands — not cosmetic work, but load-bearing function.",
          "This is not the phase to chase visible abs or burn yourself into the ground. Strength comes first. Movement quality comes first.",
          "Controlled eccentrics, honest RPEs, and zero junk volume are non-negotiable. The discipline you show here compounds later."
        ],
        "outcomes": [
          "Noticeable strength increases in squat, hinge, press, and row patterns",
          "Improved trunk stability and confidence under load",
          "Established training consistency and momentum across four sessions per week",
          "Clear progress in foundational lifts despite operating in a caloric deficit"
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "num": 2,
      "name": "VOLUME ENGINE",
      "tagline": "Force the Adaptation",
      "weeks": "Weeks 6–10",
      "focuses": [
        "Increase hypertrophy volume per muscle group through higher training density and shorter rest periods.",
        "Advance core loading to weighted and hanging variations while introducing structured conditioning blocks."
      ],
      "teaser": {
        "subtitle": "The foundation stays. The workload explodes.",
        "paragraphs": [
          "Cycle 2 transforms your strength base into visible muscle through higher training density and significantly increased hypertrophy volume.",
          "Rest periods shorten, weekly sets per muscle climb, and sessions demand sustained output rather than isolated effort.",
          "Core training evolves from simple loading into weighted and hanging variations, while structured conditioning blocks accelerate fat loss without eroding muscle.",
          "Complete this cycle as written and progress your loads. What follows rewards those who built properly — and finished everything."
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "num": 3,
      "name": "METABOLIC OVERRIDE",
      "tagline": "Burn Without Breakdown",
      "weeks": "Weeks 11–16",
      "focuses": [
        "Maximise energy expenditure through high-density supersets and circuit-based resistance training while preserving muscle.",
        "Peak direct abdominal volume and introduce advanced anti-extension and trunk control progressions."
      ]
    },
    {
      "num": 4,
      "name": "STRENGTH RECLAIM",
      "tagline": "Hold the Line",
      "weeks": "Weeks 17–21",
      "focuses": [
        "Restore and surpass early-cycle strength levels with reduced volume and higher intensity to protect lean mass.",
        "Reduce conditioning volume and refine muscular detail through isolation and contraction-focused work."
      ]
    },
    {
      "num": 5,
      "name": "THE REVEAL",
      "tagline": "Maintain What You Earned",
      "weeks": "Weeks 22–26",
      "focuses": [
        "Maintain peak strength while reducing fatigue and bringing body composition to target condition.",
        "Transition to maintenance intake and stress-test the physique, habits, and systems that sustain long-term results."
      ]
    }
  ],
